# Examples and Plugin System

## Examples Directory
The project includes standalone examples in [examples/](mdc:examples/):

- [examples/gpu_examples.zig](mdc:examples/gpu_examples.zig) - GPU acceleration examples
- [examples/neural.zig](mdc:examples/neural.zig) - Neural network examples
- [examples/weather.zig](mdc:examples/weather.zig) - Weather API integration
- [examples/plugins/](mdc:examples/plugins/) - Plugin examples

## Plugin System
The project includes a comprehensive plugin system in [src/plugins/](mdc:src/plugins/):

- [src/plugins/interface.zig](mdc:src/plugins/interface.zig) - Plugin interface definitions
- [src/plugins/loader.zig](mdc:src/plugins/loader.zig) - Plugin loading and management
- [src/plugins/registry.zig](mdc:src/plugins/registry.zig) - Plugin registry and discovery
- [src/plugins/types.zig](mdc:src/plugins/types.zig) - Plugin type definitions

## Example Guidelines

### Standalone Examples
- Each example should be self-contained and runnable
- Include clear documentation and usage instructions
- Demonstrate key features and capabilities
- Use realistic data and scenarios

### Code Examples
```zig
const std = @import("std");
const database = @import("database");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();
    const allocator = gpa.allocator();
    
    // Example code here
    var db = try database.Db.open("example.wdbx", true);
    defer db.close();
}
```

## Plugin Development

### Plugin Interface
```zig
pub const PluginInterface = struct {
    name: []const u8,
    version: []const u8,
    init: *const fn (allocator: std.mem.Allocator) anyerror!*Plugin,
    deinit: *const fn (plugin: *Plugin) void,
    process: *const fn (plugin: *Plugin, input: []const u8) anyerror![]u8,
};
```

### Plugin Implementation
- Implement the required interface functions
- Handle memory management properly
- Include error handling for all operations
- Provide clear documentation and examples

## Best Practices

### Examples
- Keep examples simple and focused
- Include error handling and cleanup
- Use descriptive variable names
- Comment complex operations
- Test examples regularly

### Plugins
- Follow the established plugin interface
- Use proper memory management
- Include comprehensive error handling
- Provide clear documentation
- Test plugins thoroughly

## Plugin Registry
- Register plugins with descriptive names
- Include version information
- Provide metadata for plugin discovery
- Support plugin dependencies
- Handle plugin loading errors gracefully

## Testing
- Test examples with various inputs
- Verify plugin loading and unloading
- Test plugin error handling
- Include integration tests for plugins
- Verify memory management in plugins